class Solution {
public:
    int rangeBitwiseAnd(int left, int right) {
        int shift = 0;
        while (left < right) {
            left >>= 1;
            right >>= 1;
            shift++;
        }
        return left << shift;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
explanation: The solution works by shifting both numbers to the right until they are equal, effectively removing the bits that are different between the two numbers. The number of shifts is tracked, and the result is obtained by shifting the equalized number back to its original position. This approach takes advantage of the property that the bitwise AND of a range of numbers will be the common prefix of the binary representation of the numbers in the range.

